.TH "request_key_rcu" 9 "request_key_rcu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
request_key_rcu \- Request key from RCU-read-locked context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct key *" request_key_rcu
.BI "(struct key_type *type "  ","
.BI "const char *description "  ","
.BI "struct key_tag *domain_tag "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "type" 12
The type of key we want.
.IP "description" 12
The name of the key we want.
.IP "domain_tag" 12
The domain in which the key operates.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Request a key from a context that we may not sleep in (such as RCU-mode
pathwalk).  Keys under construction are ignored.

Return a pointer to the found key if successful, -ENOKEY if we couldn't find
a key or some other error if the key found was unsuitable or inaccessible.
